This dish was FANTASTIC. However, I did increase the sauce to 2 3/4 cups of sauce instead of 2 1/2. It was Perfect!

Rating: 4
This casserole is wonderful! The first time I made it, I cooked it for the suggested 45 minutes. The top was very crunchy; really too crunchy for my taste. The second time I made it, I only baked it 40 minutes. The results were much better - rigatoni was not so dry and not nearly as crunchy. I think adding calamata olives would be good, too.

Rating: 4
Very good. Also used a little more sauce, and added some crushed red pepper to the onions while sauteeing. Good quality, fresh mozzarella really makes the dish.

Rating: 4
This was fabulous. I did use more sauce than called for, simply because I like my pasta saucy. I highly recommend using fresh mozzarella for this recipe and the only thing I will change when I make this again someday will be to thin my somewhat thick homemade marinara sauce. While baking in the oven, the pasta absorbed some of the moisture and the rigatoni on top got a little dry. Otherwise terrific.